00:08:01.280 --> 00:08:04.110 align:middle line:84%
the more it grabbed me and said,
yes, this is where you belong.

00:08:04.110 --> 00:08:05.720 align:middle line:90%
And I went home, so to speak.

00:08:05.720 --> 00:08:07.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:08:07.060 --> 00:08:09.740 align:middle line:84%
Now you're going to give us some
facts about acupuncture that

00:08:09.740 --> 00:08:10.890 align:middle line:90%
would be helpful.

00:08:10.890 --> 00:08:11.690 align:middle line:90%
I love this.

00:08:11.690 --> 00:08:14.030 align:middle line:10%
I didn't realize that
every single acupuncture

00:08:14.030 --> 00:08:18.330 align:middle line:10%
point has a name addressed
to it, like Heavenly Well.

00:08:18.330 --> 00:08:19.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:08:19.130 --> 00:08:23.780 align:middle line:84%
The Chinese were-- number
one, the ancient Chinese

00:08:23.780 --> 00:08:25.790 align:middle line:84%
didn't have things
that distracted them

00:08:25.790 --> 00:08:27.560 align:middle line:90%
from the oneness of nature.

00:08:27.560 --> 00:08:31.225 align:middle line:84%
They didn't have cable
TV, and fast food places,

00:08:31.225 --> 00:08:32.100 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:08:32.100 --> 00:08:34.130 align:middle line:84%
So they were more in
harmony with themselves

00:08:34.130 --> 00:08:35.750 align:middle line:90%
and their surroundings.

00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:40.250 align:middle line:84%
And through observation, at
length, thousands of years

00:08:40.250 --> 00:08:43.610 align:middle line:84%
literally, they realized that
not only was acupuncture good

00:08:43.610 --> 00:08:44.960 align:middle line:90%
for pain--

00:08:44.960 --> 00:08:46.550 align:middle line:84%
number one, acupuncture
was originally

00:08:46.550 --> 00:08:48.530 align:middle line:90%
used as a preventative medicine.

00:08:48.530 --> 00:08:51.140 align:middle line:10%
In ancient China, the
health care practitioner

00:08:51.140 --> 00:08:52.970 align:middle line:10%
provided the service
and they only

00:08:52.970 --> 00:08:55.050 align:middle line:10%
got paid as long as the
patient was healthy.

00:08:55.050 --> 00:08:57.230 align:middle line:84%
As soon as the
patient became ill,

00:08:57.230 --> 00:08:59.720 align:middle line:84%
they stopped paying until
they became healthy again.

00:08:59.720 --> 00:09:03.470 align:middle line:84%
But the ancient Chinese
were very, very observant.

00:09:03.470 --> 00:09:04.970 align:middle line:84%
And they realized
that not only were

00:09:04.970 --> 00:09:08.450 align:middle line:84%
certain points good
for the physical aspect

00:09:08.450 --> 00:09:11.540 align:middle line:84%
of the treatment, but
they also addressed

00:09:11.540 --> 00:09:14.090 align:middle line:90%
the mental and emotional states.

00:09:14.090 --> 00:09:16.460 align:middle line:84%
So a point like
Heavenly Well is not--

00:09:16.460 --> 00:09:18.660 align:middle line:84%
which, it's found right
now the elbow, by the way.

00:09:18.660 --> 00:09:20.480 align:middle line:84%
It's not only good
for, say, tennis

00:09:20.480 --> 00:09:24.350 align:middle line:84%
elbow and joint situations,
that sort of thing,

00:09:24.350 --> 00:09:29.342 align:middle line:84%
but it's a place where mentally
you can go and be refreshed.

00:09:29.342 --> 00:09:30.800 align:middle line:84%
It's sort of an
oasis, if you will.

00:09:30.800 --> 00:09:34.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, we have a chart
that just shows, again,

00:09:34.380 --> 00:09:37.430 align:middle line:84%
the meridians, OK, the lines,
the points, and so forth.

00:09:37.430 --> 00:09:40.670 align:middle line:84%
And, as you said,
this is just, then--

00:09:40.670 --> 00:09:43.670 align:middle line:84%
every single one of
these points have

00:09:43.670 --> 00:09:45.210 align:middle line:90%
energy flowing through them.

00:09:45.210 --> 00:09:50.740 align:middle line:84%
>> There are 365 points,
which is interesting, 365.

00:09:50.740 --> 00:09:53.210 align:middle line:84%
And, actually, depending
on the tradition,

00:09:53.210 --> 00:09:55.100 align:middle line:90%
there can be a few extra points.

00:09:55.100 --> 00:09:58.790 align:middle line:84%
But the idea is that energy
flows through the body.

00:09:58.790 --> 00:10:01.140 align:middle line:90%
It saturates the entire body.

00:10:01.140 --> 00:10:04.680 align:middle line:84%
But in the acupuncture
meridians, it's concentrated.

00:10:04.680 --> 00:10:07.370 align:middle line:10%
And it flows along
very specific channels.

00:10:07.370 --> 00:10:09.890 align:middle line:84%
And at various points
along those channels

00:10:09.890 --> 00:10:12.620 align:middle line:84%
it comes close to the
surface of the skin.

00:10:12.620 --> 00:10:15.920 align:middle line:84%
And that is where you can access
the energy through acupuncture

00:10:15.920 --> 00:10:16.760 align:middle line:90%
needles.

00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:17.750 align:middle line:90%
Those are the points.

00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:20.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, you said the most
significant points are between

00:10:20.270 --> 00:10:22.430 align:middle line:90%
the elbow and the fingertips.

00:10:22.430 --> 00:10:25.250 align:middle line:10%
>> I can't say one is more
significant than the other,

00:10:25.250 --> 00:10:28.340 align:middle line:10%
but these are the points that
are most frequently used--

00:10:28.340 --> 00:10:31.340 align:middle line:10%
between the elbow and the
fingertips and the knees

00:10:31.340 --> 00:10:32.570 align:middle line:10%
and the toes.

00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:34.250 align:middle line:10%
They're what's called
command points.

00:10:34.250 --> 00:10:35.250 align:middle line:10%
>> Most frequently used.

00:10:35.250 --> 00:10:36.050 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes.

00:10:36.050 --> 00:10:37.150 align:middle line:10%
>> OK.

00:10:37.150 --> 00:10:39.520 align:middle line:10%
Now, do they relate to
other parts of the body?

00:10:39.520 --> 00:10:42.325 align:middle line:84%
Is it like the
reflexology concept, here?

00:10:42.325 --> 00:10:44.200 align:middle line:84%
>> They do relate to
other parts of the body.

00:10:44.200 --> 00:10:47.060 align:middle line:84%
Someone that has a headache
may get a needle in their leg.

00:10:47.060 --> 00:10:47.290 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:10:47.290 --> 00:10:47.670 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:10:47.670 --> 00:10:48.050 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:48.050 --> 00:10:48.250 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:10:48.250 --> 00:10:50.520 align:middle line:84%
>> So, yeah, it depends
on what's called for with

00:10:50.520 --> 00:10:52.040 align:middle line:90%
a particular individual.

00:10:52.040 --> 00:10:54.505 align:middle line:84%
>> So as you studied
this and you just--

00:10:54.505 --> 00:10:58.240 align:middle line:84%
it was just natural to you
and you just felt an affinity

00:10:58.240 --> 00:11:00.010 align:middle line:84%
