approach to health?

00:11:00.010 --> 00:11:00.970 align:middle line:90%
>> I felt an affinity.

00:11:00.970 --> 00:11:03.040 align:middle line:90%
I'm not sure how natural it was.

00:11:03.040 --> 00:11:04.415 align:middle line:90%
It's something I've worked at.

00:11:04.415 --> 00:11:06.250 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've really
had to work at it.

00:11:06.250 --> 00:11:09.670 align:middle line:84%
If there was some latent talent,
then I had to cultivate it.

00:11:09.670 --> 00:11:12.240 align:middle line:84%
It's not something
that sprang up.

00:11:12.240 --> 00:11:13.990 align:middle line:84%
And that's the way it
is with some people.

00:11:13.990 --> 00:11:16.032 align:middle line:84%
Some people know immediately
what they want to do

00:11:16.032 --> 00:11:17.710 align:middle line:84%
and they're very
good at it and it

00:11:17.710 --> 00:11:19.150 align:middle line:90%
seems to come natural to them.

00:11:19.150 --> 00:11:22.450 align:middle line:84%
Others of us have to work
at developing our skills

00:11:22.450 --> 00:11:23.770 align:middle line:90%
a little more diligently.

00:11:23.770 --> 00:11:26.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I like the idea,
too, that you had a personal

00:11:26.110 --> 00:11:28.450 align:middle line:84%
experience of it when
you were living in Korea,

00:11:28.450 --> 00:11:31.970 align:middle line:84%
where you actually saw it used
and you saw the success of it.

00:11:31.970 --> 00:11:32.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:11:32.770 --> 00:11:36.040 align:middle line:84%
>> And that must have just,
then, kind of stayed with you.

00:11:36.040 --> 00:11:39.130 align:middle line:84%
>> It was a friend of mine
who got sick one night.

00:11:39.130 --> 00:11:42.940 align:middle line:84%
I think it was a deep fried
chicken that he had eaten.

00:11:42.940 --> 00:11:45.940 align:middle line:84%
And he was literally
on his hands and knees

00:11:45.940 --> 00:11:49.000 align:middle line:84%
