00:13:39.280 --> 00:13:41.620 align:middle line:84%
We have a graphic
that just says chi.

00:13:41.620 --> 00:13:45.490 align:middle line:10%
And it is what you said was
like the romanesque approach

00:13:45.490 --> 00:13:47.770 align:middle line:10%
to the language, the
Chinese language.

00:13:47.770 --> 00:13:50.950 align:middle line:10%
And chi then, C-H-I, is
what most people see.

00:13:50.950 --> 00:13:52.320 align:middle line:90%
We think of that is energy.

00:13:52.320 --> 00:13:56.640 align:middle line:90%
Is that the definition of chi?

00:13:56.640 --> 00:14:00.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Chi actually has a
number of definitions.

00:14:00.130 --> 00:14:02.180 align:middle line:10%
Life force is
certainly one of them.

00:14:02.180 --> 00:14:03.580 align:middle line:10%
The breath is another.

00:14:03.580 --> 00:14:07.750 align:middle line:10%
Anything that has the potential
to animate is, yet, another.

00:14:07.750 --> 00:14:15.040 align:middle line:10%
The Chinese idogram for chi
is a pot of rice, boiling.

00:14:15.040 --> 00:14:17.320 align:middle line:84%
And the steam
coming off the rice

00:14:17.320 --> 00:14:19.300 align:middle line:84%
represents the
energy that's derived

00:14:19.300 --> 00:14:21.370 align:middle line:90%
from grain, in this case.

00:14:21.370 --> 00:14:24.130 align:middle line:90%
And it moves.

00:14:24.130 --> 00:14:25.960 align:middle line:90%
It's the movement of life.

00:14:25.960 --> 00:14:26.790 align:middle line:90%
Its animation.

00:14:26.790 --> 00:14:28.020 align:middle line:90%
Its being alive.

00:14:28.020 --> 00:14:32.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Now qigong is with
the Q-I, is another--

00:14:32.530 --> 00:14:34.210 align:middle line:84%
is the preferred
Chinese spelling

00:14:34.210 --> 00:14:35.410 align:middle line:90%
of the same thing, the--

00:14:35.410 --> 00:14:35.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Right

00:14:35.870 --> 00:14:36.670 align:middle line:90%
>> --the Q-I.

00:14:36.670 --> 00:14:39.460 align:middle line:84%
>> The first spelling is
what's called Wade-Giles,

00:14:39.460 --> 00:14:42.340 align:middle line:84%
which was the first Romanization
of the Chinese language that

00:14:42.340 --> 00:14:45.280 align:middle line:90%
was used on a wide basis.

00:14:45.280 --> 00:14:46.870 align:middle line:84%
The Chinese came
along and developed

00:14:46.870 --> 00:14:50.350 align:middle line:84%
what's called Pinion, which is
their official Romanization.

00:14:50.350 --> 00:14:51.950 align:middle line:90%
And they spelled it Q-I.

00:14:51.950 --> 00:14:52.750 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:14:52.750 --> 00:14:53.770 align:middle line:90%
And what is qigong?

00:14:53.770 --> 00:14:57.250 align:middle line:84%
If you were to give us a one
liner on qigong, what is it?

00:14:57.250 --> 00:15:01.390 align:middle line:84%
>> The act of cultivating
one's personal energy.

00:15:01.390 --> 00:15:02.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, OK.

00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:05.410 align:middle line:84%
So you have done a
demonstration with us.

