are done very slowly.

00:15:21.650 --> 00:15:24.130 align:middle line:84%
There are some that are done
with some rapidity, though.

00:15:24.130 --> 00:15:25.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, the one
that you have done,

00:15:25.930 --> 00:15:28.430 align:middle line:84%
we want the audience
to do along with us.

00:15:28.430 --> 00:15:30.490 align:middle line:10%
But what is the
exercise that we're

00:15:30.490 --> 00:15:33.130 align:middle line:10%
about to see that
you have done for us?

00:15:33.130 --> 00:15:37.000 align:middle line:84%
>> This particular exercise
doesn't have a specific name.

00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:40.090 align:middle line:84%
But, in my experience,
it's the one exercise

00:15:40.090 --> 00:15:44.320 align:middle line:84%
that I've found where, in a
fairly short period of time--

00:15:44.320 --> 00:15:48.250 align:middle line:84%
typically, my classes
are around 20 people.

00:15:48.250 --> 00:15:51.640 align:middle line:84%
18 or 19 of the 20 people
will feel their own energy

00:15:51.640 --> 00:15:52.570 align:middle line:90%
with this exercise.

00:15:52.570 --> 00:15:54.520 align:middle line:84%
And I've never had that
sort of success rate

00:15:54.520 --> 00:15:57.250 align:middle line:84%
with any other one exercise in
such a short period of time.

00:15:57.250 --> 00:16:00.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Someone in our audience that
does this with you should be

00:16:00.230 --> 00:16:01.480 align:middle line:90%
able to feel their own energy.

00:16:01.480 --> 00:16:01.930 align:middle line:90%
>> More than likely.

00:16:01.930 --> 00:16:03.760 align:middle line:84%
>> So we're going
to watch this now.

00:16:03.760 --> 00:16:06.850 align:middle line:84%
And it is in slow,
very slow motion.

00:16:06.850 --> 00:16:08.950 align:middle line:90%
Tell us what you're doing now.

00:16:08.950 --> 00:16:10.780 align:middle line:90%
>> This is a commencement form.

00:16:10.780 --> 00:16:14.290 align:middle line:84%
I am basically gathering my
energy and bringing it down.

00:16:14.290 --> 00:16:16.360 align:middle line:90%
Energy has a tendency to rise.

00:16:16.360 --> 00:16:18.690 align:middle line:84%
If you think of
heat, heat rises.

00:16:18.690 --> 00:16:22.450 align:middle line:84%
So I'm bringing it down and I'm
settling it in what the Chinese

00:16:22.450 --> 00:16:26.890 align:middle line:84%
refer to as the dan t'ian, which
translates as-- essentially

00:16:26.890 --> 00:16:30.250 align:middle line:84%
as a lower elixir
field or sea of chi.

00:16:30.250 --> 00:16:34.420 align:middle line:84%
It's where the energy supposedly
is rooted in the body, right

00:16:34.420 --> 00:16:36.235 align:middle line:90%
just below the navel area.

00:16:36.235 --> 00:16:38.980 align:middle line:84%
Now, right now
I'm just focusing.

00:16:38.980 --> 00:16:41.830 align:middle line:90%
And I'm compacting my chi.

00:16:41.830 --> 00:16:47.020 align:middle line:84%
In other words, I'm trying
to concentrate it on the arms

00:16:47.020 --> 00:16:48.580 align:middle line:90%
or in my arms.

00:16:48.580 --> 00:16:54.070 align:middle line:84%
Right here, I'm crossing my
arms at two strategic points.

00:16:54.070 --> 00:16:56.260 align:middle line:84%
Just inside my right
wrist is a point

00:16:56.260 --> 00:16:58.210 align:middle line:90%
known as Inner Frontier Gate.

00:16:58.210 --> 00:17:02.980 align:middle line:84%
And on the outside of my left
wrist is Outer Frontier Gate.

00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:06.250 align:middle line:84%
